*Learning Before Knowing*

*Author:* Nishit Ram
*Pinternship ID:* WIN25987

I joined the Pinternship with no real understanding of the MERN stack and very little clarity about how real-world development learning actually works. Everything felt unfamiliar at first—the tools, the concepts, even the way problems were framed. I wasn’t confident, but I was willing to begin.

What gradually changed my perspective was the learning approach through the ViBe platform. It wasn’t about passively watching and moving on. It required me to try, fail, reflect, and figure things out on my own. That process wasn’t easy, but it was honest. Over time, my confidence grew—not because I knew everything, but because I learned *how to learn*.

Since the internship is MERN-based, working with documentation became a daily habit. Earlier, documentation felt overwhelming and confusing. Now, it feels like a guide. I learned how to read it patiently, search with intent, and connect it directly to what I was building. That shift fundamentally changed the way I approach problem-solving.

The daily stand-ups with **Prof. Sudarshan Iyengar Sir** brought structure and accountability to each day. They never felt like pressure. Listening to others share their struggles and progress reminded me that learning looks different for everyone—and that consistency matters far more than speed.

Breakout sessions added another meaningful layer to the experience. Interacting with peers and senior interns, exchanging ideas, discussing doubts, and learning from diverse perspectives made the environment collaborative rather than competitive. Connecting with people from different parts of the country made the journey even more enriching.

At this point, I’ve completed the ViBe course and progressed steadily through the case studies. More importantly, I’ve become comfortable with the process. I no longer rush to understand everything instantly. I take my time, experiment, and trust that clarity will come.

This Pinternship has helped me build confidence, consistency, and a healthier mindset toward learning. I’m grateful to VLED Lab, *Nandan Prabhudesai Sir*, and the entire team—Meenakshi Ma’am, Bhavna Ma’am, Nitin Sir, and Rohit Sir—for creating such a supportive and thoughtfully structured learning space.

This experience has genuinely changed how I learn, think, and grow—and I’m excited for what comes next.

